position that the burden on heavily indebted countries is becoming 
unsustainable and such initiatives as the recent mexican 
debtforbonds swap are needed if the debt crisis is ever to be 
resolved in that case mexico offered to exchange debt held by 
commerical banks in return for a reduced amount of mexican bonds 
which were backed by us treasury securities 
for his part baker has also endorsed efforts to find new ways 
of reducing the debt burden but he has opposed any broad 
debtrelief plans involving the world bank or the imf contending 
they would be too costly and would represent a bailout for big 
commercial banks 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

