last week to put warning labels on alcoholic beverage containers in 
the state 
the bottom line is that alcohol is still the nations drug of 
choice and a major health problem especially among young people 
she said 
a recent gallup poll showed that the number of adults who 
believe that alcohol is a problem in their homes has doubled since 
1974 to 24 percent 
in 1980 per person consumption was 25 gallons of liquor 26 
gallons of wine and 307 gallons of beer in 1985 liquor use 
dropped to 22 gallons beer eased off to 296 gallons but wine 
consumption rose to 29 gallons 
eddie burke coowner of doyles an irish pub in boston said 
the bar now sells five cases of nonalcoholic beer weekly while 
three years ago there were no takers 
people are just drinking less although theyre drinking more 
