states which will be on display in the gallerys east building 
until sept 5 then they will go to the institute of arts at 
minneapolis minn where many immigrants from sweden settled they 
will be on view there from oct 9 to jan 1 1989 
the baroque period in sweden is largely unfamiliar to the 
american public and we expect this exhibition to open up a 
fascinating area of european history to this country j carter 
brown director of the national gallery said 
