the plant closings provision is one facet of a sweeping bill 
that contains measures ranging from approval for the administration 
to sign trade deals with other countries to repeal of the windfall 
profits tax on oil companies 
at the heart of the bill are provisions that restructure the way 
in which the united states retaliates against violations of 
international trade rules lawmakers say they are designed to open 
foreign markets to us exports 
