veto most likely would have to start with bentsen under powers that 
have been granted him by senate conferees 
bentsen as vice chairman of the conference committee took the 
lead in dropping a number of stringent provisions opposed earlier 
by the reagan administration 
the administration has been describing the plantclosings 
provision as one that would be disastrously expensive for industry 
while the measure contains no money provisions some business 
groups have suggested it would be a first step toward substantial 
costs later 
