<TEXT>
even though eastwest relations have 
thawed communist espionage is on the rise in west germany and 
probably is aimed more at hightech industrial secrets than 
military or political ones officials say 
west germany has been infested with communist spies since its 
creation in 1949 in the ashes of world war ii the spying has 
ranged from east german truck drivers rolling through the 
countryside to moles in the highest of government offices 
among the most important spies caught were guenter guillaume 
who wrecked chancellor willy brandts government in 1974 margret 
hoeke who was a secretary to five presidents and manfred rotsch 
who delivered topsecret nato documents to the soviets 
but just last month west german federal police arrested 11 
people suspected of working for the kgb the soviet intelligence 
agency and are investigating others 
the large number of arrests confirms that instead of 
refraining from activating agents in a time of detente the east 
bloc is intensifying its espionage activities interior minister 
friedrich zimmermann told reporters after the march sweep 
hansgert lange spokesman for the office for the protection of 
the constitution west germanys counterespionage agency said 
warmer eastwest relations increase the opportunities for spying 
the thaw has increased interest in obtaining information and 
also improved conditions for espionage lange said in an 
interview at his cologne office 
lange added that because some communist countries have loosened 
emigration restrictions a danger increases that agents have been 
planted among the refugees 
emigration plays an important role in espionage in the federal 
republic west germany as has been shown by the arrest of the 
suspected kgb agents lange said 
among the 11 suspects arrested in march were four soviet emigres 
with communist research lagging behind the west in many areas 
soviet bloc agents have intensified their efforts to obtain secrets 
from private companies in science and hightech fields lange said 
the interest in political secrets is still great but for 
technological and scientific matters it has grown considerably 
lange said 
security officials estimate that as many as 3000 spies are at 
work in west germany most of them from east germany between 30 
and 50 suspected spies are arrested each year the 
counterintelligence office says 
secretaries and other government employees in bonn the nations 
capital are among those who have been caught 
also security officials have long suspected that east german 
truckers driving through west germany report on military movements 
and gather other information for the east german secret service 
but a spy can come from anywhere 
west germany automatically grants citizenship to all ethnic 
german refugees from the east bloc making the task of isolating 
communist agents extremely difficult 
in addition west germany and east germany have improved 
relations over the past few years resulting in more contacts 
between the two sides and greater chances for espionage 
east german authorities have allowed the resettling of its 
citizens to west germany to increase dramatically reaching a high 
of 30000 in 1984 compared to just 7000 the year before 
according to federal statistics 
past spy scandals have damaged the nations image among other 
nato allies 
west germany arrested 16 communist agents in 1976 after cracking 
east german infiltration methods but it turned out that two of the 
spies lotharerwin lutze and his wife renate had been passing 
nato documents to east germany since the 1960s west german defense 
minister georg leber resigned over that scandal 
in 1974 guenter guillaume a close aide to chancellor brandt 
was exposed as an east german agent and brandt resigned 
guillaume began serving a 13year jail sentence in 1975 the 
longest ever given by a west german court to a convicted spy but 
he was released six years later in an exchange of agents with east 
germany 
in 1985 the constititution protection office itself was rocked 
by the defection to east germany of hansjoachim tiedge who headed 
an agency group responsible for catching east german spies 
security officials believe many of the communist agents in west 
germany now can do only minor damage 
but one must be careful when one uses the term small fish 
said lange a small fish can always become a bigger one 
</TEXT>
