domestic airline flights of two hours or less beginning april 23 is 
a good first step but contains loopholes 
because congress used a time limit rather than mileage airline 
flights scheduled for just under two hours could escape compliance 
he said flight time can be altered by the rate of climb flight 
altitude the type of aircraft being used headwinds and the 
schedule of the airports involved leichtman said 
the federal ban on smoking during shortterm flights will expire 
in two years if congress takes no further action but leichtman 
