a share 
revenue fell 5 percent to 24 billion from 25 billion 
commission revenues a significant portion of merrill lynchs 
business fell 33 percent to 440 million from the yearearlier 
record quarterly total of 654 million which the company 
attributed to reduced stock market activity 
like other investment giants reacting to the october crash 
merrill lynch instituted or accelerated staffing and cost 
reductions anticipating leaner times in what historically has been 
a cyclical business 
