<TEXT>
jim s gilmore jrs office looks more 
like the winners circle at the indianapolis 500 than corporate 
headquarters for his 200 millionayear business empire 
visitors have a hard time figuring out the color of the wall 
paint photographs and paintings of race cars and triumphant 
drivers accepting roses and trophies cover the office walls and 
line the corridors from floor to ceiling 
but gilmore isnt in the racing business at least not for a 
profit 
most of gilmores income is generated by his broadcasting 
corporation and automobile dealerships 
his success in those areas has allowed gilmore to pursue his 
lifelong passion for auto racing a preoccupation he adopted from 
his father in 1973 gilmore signed on friend and indy 500 champion 
aj foyt creating the gilmorefoyt racing team 
one of the greatest moments in my life was when aj won the 
indy 500 for the fourth time in 1977 said gilmore 61 a 
cheerful grayhaired man whose blue eyes ignite with excitement 
each time he mentions racing 
the feeling is obviously mutual with foyt 
i cant say enough about jim hes stuck by me through thick 
and thin said foyt who 15 years later continues to drive 
gilmorebacked cars 
though backing a winner in the indy 500 was a new experience 
gilmore was already well accustomed to corporate victory from his 
grandfathers profitable downtown kalamazoo department store 
gilmore brothers gilmore has created a diverse business empire 
with about 1000 employees 
of his three auto dealerships the one in miami fla is 
consistently among the top four chevrolet dealerships in the 
country selling as many as 21000 cars each year gilmore says 
gilmore also recently announced he would become a partner in foyts 
chevrolet dealership in houston 
gilmore owns two midwest television stations weht in 
evansville ind and kodetv in joplin mo and two florida radio 
stations wlve in miami and wivy in jacksonville 
then theres all that real estate in downtown kalamazoo 
including several office buildings and parking lots and the 
2700acre hog farm in northern kalamazoo county 
and more gilmore also owns an insurance company is director of 
a kalamazoo plastics manufacturer and sits on the boards of two 
banks he is a partner in the parent company of the kalamazoo wings 
hockey team and partowner of their stadium he also has minority 
interests in a kalamazoo advertising firm and an automotive 
engineering company in daytona fla 
as if that werent enough to keep him busy gilmore serves on 
dozens of local state and national commissions ranging from the 
presidents council on sports and physical fitness to the local 
chamber of commerce 
the parent company for his holdings jim gilmore enterprises 
has had annual revenues as high as 300 million 
in 1985 forbes listed gilmore as one of the 400 wealthiest 
americans estimating his worth at 160 million 
forbes was close but a little on the high side gilmore 
says with a smile 
maybe so but its still not bad for a firstyear college 
dropout who started out by mopping floors at the family department 
store 
gilmore is quick to admit that most of the money he started out 
with was inherited after his grandfather died his grandmother 
married the founder of upjohn co the pharmaceutical company 
merging kalamazoos two wealthiest families 
but gilmores workaholic and perfectionist tendencies have 
allowed him to make the most of his head start 
after growing tired of working in the familys department store 
gilmore was elected kalamazoos youngest mayor a position he held 
from 195961 
a diehard republican gilmore remained active in politics for 
many years heading five congressional campaigns for former rep 
garry e brown gilmore also made an unsuccessful bid of his own 
for a congressional seat in 1980 two years after his first wife 
died of cancer 
running was one of the best things i did in my life although 
losing didnt feel very good said gilmore the father of five 
grown children and stepfather to his second wifes four children 
though gilmore contends he has no plans to get back into the 
political arena he may be lured to washington dc if his good 
friend of 12 years vice president george bush is elected 
president in november 
i think were good enough friends that theres a good 
possibility i might be asked to do something in a bush 
administration gilmore said 
gilmore the public servant also believes in continuing his 
familys tradition of philanthropy instead of sharing his profits 
with the community through a foundation after his death gilmore 
says he believes in working on things while were still alive 
every night when i get home from work i put on a sweater and 
take a walk downtown and i take notes on things that need to be 
done he said 
and he doesnt believe in procrastination for example when a 
kalamazoo homeless shelter needed repairs late last year gilmore 
donated 30000 for an immediate renovation 
maybe thats why aj foyt gave gilmore the diamondstudded ring 
that went with his indy victory 
when he gave it to me he said jim you may lose everything 
else but you wont lose this 
