<TEXT>
japans trade surplus continued to decline from 
yearearlier levels in march although it widened from februarys 
surplus the finance ministry announced monday 
the surplus totaled 7458 billion down from 8050 billion in 
march 1987 bu up from 5238 billion the previous month 
after seasonal adjustment the surplus came to 6552 billion 
up from 6479 billion in the previous month 
japan registered a trade surplus of 34 billion with the united 
states down from 377 billion a year earlier 
finance ministry officials characterized the figures as 
encouraging because of the yeartoyear decline 
the continuing shrinkage in the latest report was attributed to 
the high yen which has slowed the growth of exports while boosting 
the yens purchasing power and the value of imports flowing into 
the country 
imports surged much faster than exports rising 35 percent to 
1521 billion from 1126 billion a year earlier 
exports grew by a comparatively muted 174 percent to 2267 
billion from 1931 billion a year earlier 
seasonally adjusted imports in the month dipped 39 percent to 
1476 billion from 1536 billion in february while adjusted 
exports inched down 24 percent to 2131 billion from 2184 
billion 
exports to the united states rose 158 percent to 717 billion 
while american imports rose 558 percent to 377 billion 
motor vehicle imports from the united states soared 1127 
percent from a year earlier to 2001 million food imports rose 
471 percent to 8051 million while textile imports surged 878 
percent to 786 million 
japans exports of passenger vehicles to the united states rose 
56 percent to 129 billion overall electrical machinery exports 
were up 114 percent to 157 billion although television set 
exports fell 23 percent to 2738 million 
</TEXT>
