of new york co said its profit rose to 524 million or 271 a 
share in the first quarter compared with 286 million or 151 a 
share a year earlier 
chairman joseph a rice said the results included 123 million 
in tax benefits related to the loanloss provisions that the 
company took in 1987 in anticipation of problems in collecting some 
third world loans 
