1312 million a year earlier as the difference between what the 
bank paid in interest to obtain funds and what it received on its 
money widened in the banking companys favor 
in the quarter irving took a provision for credit losses of 
196 million in 1988 compared with 218 million in 1987 that 
left its loan loss allowance at 6965 million or 438 percent of 
loans compared with 2248 million or 162 percent of loans a 
year earlier 
