japanese domestic carrier disclosed it told boeing of several 
instances of poor workmanship in 747 and 767 airliners mostly on 
newly delivered planes 
the problems included a wing flap disintegrating in flight on 
the first day of service smoke from a misassembled power unit that 
caused an emergency landing and problems in a fire extinguisher 
system all nippon said 
dean thornton head of boeing commercial airplanes was quoted 
by the newspaper as saying a jetliner is a big complicated piece 
of machinery 
the complaints were isolated instances that shouldnt 
happen he said were gonna bust our butt to make sure they 
dont happen again 
yoshiyuki funatsu all nippon executive vice president told the 
postintelligencer that problems with defects had been increasing 
recently at boeing he said that while many had been minor some 
had safety ramifications although none of the defects had caused 
accidents 
