operations told the newspaper the companys maintenance crews had 
found faulty firesuppression systems in the cargo holds of three 
767200s the system pipes firefighting chemicals to the forward 
and aft compartments of the cargo hold 
the pipes were misrouted baker said if you light them 
off for the forward belly system they go off in the rear 
baker said that after being informed of the problem by american 
boeing found one faulty system on its production line and all 
nippon and japan air lines found several in their planes 
last week it was reported that japan air lines president susumu 
yamaji had complained of manufacturing mistakes in a march 30 
letter to boeing chairman frank shrontz besides the fire 
extinguisher system the airline complained about engine 
temperature sensors being installed in reverse order in a 747 
which would cause temperature gauges to register for the wrong 
engines 
