operating income in the business publications segment fell 227 
percent to 326 million as revenue slipped 46 percent in the 
quarter partly reflecting lower levels of financial advertising in 
the wake of the october stock market crash 
operating income from the information services segment which 
includes telerate results more than fourfold to 543 million as 
revenue more than tripled 
ottaway newspapers inc the community services segment said 
its operating income rose 37 percent to 85 million as revenue 
rose 115 percent 
